==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scorpaenoid
<hw>Scor*pae"noid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>Scorpaena</ets>, a typical genus (see <er>Scorpene</er>) +
<ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the
family <fam>Scorpaenidae</fam>, which includes the scorpene, the
rosefish, the California rockfishes, and many other food fishes.
<altsp>[Written also <asp>scorpaenid</asp>.]</altsp></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scorpene</ent>⟦br⟧
